.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-47 Nostr Wallet Connect (NWC), a protocol for clients to
interact with a remote lightning wallet through encrypted nostr messages.
Communication happens via E2E\-encrypted direct messages over nostr relays
using dedicated ephemeral keys.
.PP
The protocol uses four event kinds:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBInfo event\fR (kind 13194) \- Published by the wallet service to
indicate supported capabilities.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBRequest\fR (kind 23194) \- Sent by the client to the wallet service.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBResponse\fR (kind 23195) \- Sent by the wallet service back to the
client.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBNotification\fR (kind 23197, or 23196 for NIP\-04 backwards
compatibility) \- Push notifications from the wallet service to the client.
.PP
Encryption of the content field is handled separately using
NIP\-44 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/44.md>
(preferred) or NIP\-04 (deprecated, for backwards compatibility). This module
handles the payload structure and event creation; the caller is responsible
for encrypting/decrypting the content.
.PP
Supported commands: \f(CW\*(C`pay_invoice\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`pay_keysend\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`make_invoice\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`lookup_invoice\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`list_transactions\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`get_balance\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`get_info\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`make_hold_invoice\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`cancel_hold_invoice\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`settle_hold_invoice\*(C'\fR.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS parse_uri
.IX Subsection "parse_uri"
.Vb 1
\&    my $conn = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->parse_uri($uri_string);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a \f(CW\*(C`nostr+walletconnect://\*(C'\fR connection URI. Returns a
"Connection" object. The pubkey is lowercased during parsing to
ensure consistency. Croaks if the URI is malformed or missing required
parameters (\f(CW\*(C`relay\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`secret\*(C'\fR).
.SS create_uri
.IX Subsection "create_uri"
.Vb 6
\&    my $uri = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->create_uri(
\&        wallet_pubkey => $hex_pubkey,        # required
\&        relay         => $url_or_arrayref,   # required
\&        secret        => $hex_secret,        # required
\&        lud16         => \*(Aquser@domain.com\*(Aq,  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a \f(CW\*(C`nostr+walletconnect://\*(C'\fR URI string. The \f(CW\*(C`relay\*(C'\fR parameter
accepts a single URL string or an arrayref of URLs.
.SS info_event
.IX Subsection "info_event"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->info_event(
\&        pubkey        => $wallet_pubkey,
\&        capabilities  => [qw(pay_invoice get_balance)],
\&        encryption    => [qw(nip44_v2 nip04)],      # optional
\&        notifications => [qw(payment_received)],     # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 13194 info Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`capabilities\*(C'\fR are
joined as a space\-separated string in the content field.
.SS parse_info
.IX Subsection "parse_info"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->parse_info($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 13194 info event. Returns an "Info" object. Croaks if the
event is not kind 13194. If the event has no \f(CW\*(C`encryption\*(C'\fR tag, defaults
to \f(CW\*(C`[\*(Aqnip04\*(Aq]\*(C'\fR per spec.
.SS request
.IX Subsection "request"
.Vb 4
\&    my $json = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->request(
\&        method => \*(Aqpay_invoice\*(Aq,
\&        params => { invoice => \*(Aqlnbc50n1...\*(Aq },
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Builds a JSON\-encoded request payload string. This is the content that
should be encrypted before placing in the event. Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`method\*(C'\fR or
\&\f(CW\*(C`params\*(C'\fR is missing.
.SS request_event
.IX Subsection "request_event"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->request_event(
\&        method        => \*(Aqpay_invoice\*(Aq,
\&        params        => { invoice => \*(Aqlnbc50n1...\*(Aq },
\&        pubkey        => $client_pubkey,
\&        wallet_pubkey => $wallet_pubkey,
\&        encryption    => \*(Aqnip44_v2\*(Aq,       # optional
\&        expiration    => $unix_timestamp,  # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 23194 request Net::Nostr::Event with the JSON payload
as unencrypted content (the caller should encrypt before publishing).
Includes a \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag with the wallet service pubkey, and optionally
\&\f(CW\*(C`encryption\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`expiration\*(C'\fR tags. Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR is missing or
not 64\-char lowercase hex.
.SS parse_response
.IX Subsection "parse_response"
.Vb 1
\&    my $resp = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->parse_response($json);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a decrypted JSON response payload. Returns a "Response" object.
Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`result_type\*(C'\fR is missing.
.SS response_event
.IX Subsection "response_event"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->response_event(
\&        result_type   => \*(Aqpay_invoice\*(Aq,
\&        result        => { preimage => \*(Aq...\*(Aq },  # or undef on error
\&        error         => undef,                   # or { code => \*(Aq...\*(Aq, message => \*(Aq...\*(Aq }
\&        pubkey        => $wallet_pubkey,
\&        client_pubkey => $client_pubkey,
\&        request_id    => $request_event_id,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 23195 response Net::Nostr::Event with \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags.
Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR is missing or not 64\-char lowercase hex.
.SS parse_notification
.IX Subsection "parse_notification"
.Vb 1
\&    my $notif = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->parse_notification($json);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a decrypted JSON notification payload. Returns a "Notification"
object. Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`notification_type\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`notification\*(C'\fR is missing.
.SS notification_event
.IX Subsection "notification_event"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->notification_event(
\&        notification_type => \*(Aqpayment_received\*(Aq,
\&        notification      => { type => \*(Aqincoming\*(Aq, amount => 50000 },
\&        pubkey            => $wallet_pubkey,
\&        client_pubkey     => $client_pubkey,
\&        encryption        => \*(Aqnip44_v2\*(Aq,  # or \*(Aqnip04\*(Aq for kind 23196
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a notification Net::Nostr::Event with a \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag. Uses kind 23197
by default (NIP\-44 encryption). Pass \f(CW\*(C`encryption => \*(Aqnip04\*(Aq\*(C'\fR to create
a kind 23196 event for NIP\-04 backwards compatibility. Wallet services
supporting both should publish both kinds for each notification. Croaks if
\&\f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR is missing or not 64\-char lowercase hex.
.SS validate_metadata
.IX Subsection "validate_metadata"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->validate_metadata($hashref);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that metadata does not exceed 4096 characters when JSON\-encoded.
Returns true on success, croaks on failure.
.SS validate_request
.IX Subsection "validate_request"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->validate_request($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that a request event is kind 23194 and has a \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag. Croaks
on failure.
.SS validate_response
.IX Subsection "validate_response"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->validate_response($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that a response event is kind 23195. Croaks on failure.
.SS is_expired
.IX Subsection "is_expired"
.Vb 1
\&    my $bool = Net::Nostr::WalletConnect\->is_expired($event);
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the event has an \f(CW\*(C`expiration\*(C'\fR tag with a timestamp in the
past.
.SH OBJECTS
